  <div style="margin-top:2px;" class="detail-grid">
    <div class="detail-section ab3">
      <div class="slabel">⊛ Firmware Architecture</div>
      <p class="stext">The firmware operates as a Modbus-RTU master on an Arduino Mega. A polling loop initiates a Read Holding Registers (FC 0x03) request targeting registers 0x1E–0x20 on slave address 0x01. Request frames are assembled byte-by-byte with CRC-16 appended, transmitted over UART with MAX485 direction-pin control, then the bus is switched to receive mode. The response parser validates slave address, function code, byte count, payload, and CRC before extracting the three 16-bit register values. Raw counts are decoded to ppm using the vendor voltage equation. On fault (timeout, CRC mismatch, exception code), the system logs the fault type and retries. LCD updates occur after each valid response cycle.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="detail-section abg">
      <div class="slabel">◈ Determinism &amp; Hard Real-Time Guarantees</div>
      <p class="stext">The polling loop executes at a fixed 1 Hz cadence controlled by a millis()-based scheduler — no blocking delays inside the communication path. RS-485 direction switching is performed with explicit GPIO assertion/de-assertion before and after UART transmit, ensuring no bus contention. CRC-16 is computed inline in O(n) time bounded by the fixed 8-byte request frame. The worst-case response window is bounded by the sensor's 200 ms maximum response time plus a 50 ms guard interval, giving a deterministic 250 ms timeout.</p>
    </div>
